    <h2>General</h2>
    <label for="company_name">Company Name:</label>
    <input type="text" name="company_name" required />

    <label>Geographic Location:</label>
    <input type="text" name="geographicLocation" required /><br />

    <label>Industry:</label>
    <input type="text" name="industry" required /><br />

    <label>Annual Revenue:</label>
    <input type="number" name="annualRevenue" required /><br />

    <label>Average number of employees over the past 3 years (FTE):</label>
    <input type="number" name="averageEmployees" required /><br />

    <label>New hirings over the past 3 years (FTE):</label>
    <input type="number" name="newHirings" required /><br />

    <label
      >Are the aforementioned values documented in a sustainability report
      (e.g. GRI)?</label
    >
    <select name="sustainabilityReport" required>
      <option value="a">Yes</option>
      <option value="b">Partial</option>
      <option value="c">No</option></select
    ><br />

    <label>Number of KPIs measured (across all three components)?</label>
    <select name="numberOfKPIs" required>
      <option value="a">20 or more</option>
      <option value="b">10-15</option>
      <option value="c">5 or fewer</option></select
    ><br />

    <label>Are objectives and risks sufficiently explained?</label>
    <select  name="objectivesAndRisks" required>
      <option value="a">Yes</option>
      <option value="b">Partial</option>
      <option value="c">No</option></select
    ><br />

    <label>Are plan/actual deviations presented?</label>
    <select name="planDeviations" required>
      <option value="a">Yes</option>
      <option value="b">Partial</option>
      <option value="c">No</option></select
    ><br />

    <h2>Environment</h2>
    <label
      >Energy consumption (Consumed electricity) (GWh) â€“ percentage
      renewable / percentage reduction compared to industry average:</label
    >
    <select name="energyConsumption" required>
      <option value="a">above 20%</option>
      <option value="b">10-20%</option>
      <option value="c">below 10%</option></select
    ><br />

    <label
      >Water consumption (Consumed water) (m3) percentage reduction compared
      to industry average:</label
    >
    <select name="waterConsumption" required>
      <option value="a">above 20%</option>
      <option value="b">10-20%</option>
      <option value="c">below 10%</option></select
    ><br />

    <label>Waste (Production of waste) (kg) / percentage reduction:</label>
    <select name="wasteProduction" required>
      <option value="a">above 20%</option>
      <option value="b">10-20%</option>
      <option value="c">below 10%</option></select
    ><br />

    <label>Percentage waste recycled (%):</label>
    <select name="wasteRecycled" required>
      <option value="a">above 60%</option>
      <option value="b">40-60%</option>
      <option value="c">below 40%</option></select
    ><br />

    <label
      >CO2 emissions (carbon footprint) (tCO2e) / percentage reduction
      compared to baseline year:</label
    >
    <select name="co2Emissions" required>
      <option value="a">above 20%</option>
      <option value="b">10-20%</option>
      <option value="c">below 10%</option></select
    ><br />

    <label>Number of measures to reduce the use of raw materials:</label>
    <select name="rawMaterialReduction" required>
      <option value="a">above 6</option>
      <option value="b">4-6</option>
      <option value="c">below 4</option></select
    ><br />

    <label>Number of measures to reduce CO2 emissions:</label>
    <select name="co2EmissionReduction" required>
      <option value="a">above 6</option>
      <option value="b">4-6</option>
      <option value="c">below 4</option></select
    ><br />

    <label
      >What are your development of energy costs in % of turnover?</label
    >
    <select name="energyCosts" required>
      <option value="a">5-10%</option>
      <option value="b">10-15%</option>
      <option value="c">Above 15%</option></select
    ><br />

    <label>Number of environmental accidents:</label>
    <select name="environmentalAccidents" required>
      <option value="a">Minimal to none</option>
      <option value="b">Occasional</option>
      <option value="c">Frequent</option></select
    ><br />

    <label>How energy efficient are sites/factories?</label>
    <select name="energyEfficiency" required>
      <option value="a">High</option>
      <option value="b">Moderate</option>
      <option value="c">Low</option></select
    ><br />

    <label>Percentage of reduced resource use (%):</label>
    <select name="resourceUseReduction" required>
      <option value="a">Higher than 20%</option>
      <option value="b">10-15%</option>
      <option value="c">Below 10%</option></select
    ><br />

    <label
      >CO2 emissions in relation to other market participants (%):</label
    >
    <select name="co2EmissionsMarket" required>
      <option value="a">20% or less</option>
      <option value="b">Around industry average</option>
      <option value="c">Above industry average</option></select
    ><br />

    <label>Recycling rate in relation to competitors (%):</label>
    <select name="recyclingRate" required>
      <option value="a">Higher than 20%</option>
      <option value="b">Around industry average</option>
      <option value="c">Below industry average</option></select
    ><br />

    <h2>Social</h2>
    <label
      >What is the percentage of Employee Well-being and Satisfaction in
      annual survey?</label
    >
    <select name="employeeWellBeing" required>
      <option value="a">Above 80%</option>
      <option value="b">Between 60-80%</option>
      <option value="c">Below 60%</option></select
    ><br />

    <label>What is your product recall rate?</label>
    <select name="productRecallRate" required>
      <option value="a">Less than 0.5%</option>
      <option value="b">Between 0.5% and 1%</option>
      <option value="c">More than 1%</option></select
    ><br />

    <label>Number of activities in place to improve workplace:</label>
    <select name="workplaceImprovement" required>
      <option value="a">Above 6</option>
      <option value="b">4-6</option>
      <option value="c">Below 4</option></select
    ><br />

    <label
      >Does your company have a code of conduct or policy that explicitly
      addresses human rights and labour standards?</label
    >
    <select name="humanRightsCode" required>
      <option value="a">Yes</option>
      <option value="b">Partial</option>
      <option value="c">No</option></select
    ><br />

    <label
      >In how many days do you resolve reported labour rights violations and
      provide remediation to affected workers?</label
    >
    <select name="labourRightsRemediation" required>
      <option value="a">Within 90 days</option>
      <option value="b">Within 120 days</option>
      <option value="c">Within 150 days</option></select
    ><br />

    <label
      >How frequently are assessments or audits conducted to identify and
      address potential health and safety hazards in the workplace?</label
    >
    <select name="healthSafetyAssessments" required>
      <option value="a">Monthly or bi-monthly</option>
      <option value="b">Quarterly</option>
      <option value="c">Bi-Yearly or less frequently</option></select
    ><br />

    <label
      >Does your company engage with stakeholders to understand community
      needs and align its initiatives accordingly?</label
    >
    <select name="communityEngagement" required>
      <option value="a">Yes</option>
      <option value="b">Partial</option>
      <option value="c">No</option></select
    ><br />

    <label
      >Which of the following best describes a company's approach to
      providing opportunities for skill upgrades and career
      advancement?</label
    >
    <select name="skillUpgradeApproach" required>
      <option value="a">
        Does the company actively invest in employee development programs
        and provide resources for upgrading skills, fostering a supportive
        environment for career growth?
      </option>
      <option value="b">
        Does the company offer limited opportunities for skill enhancement
        and career progression, resulting in a stagnant work environment?
      </option>
      <option value="c">
        Does the company neglect employee skill development and fail to
        provide avenues for career advancement, hindering professional
        growth within the organization?
      </option></select
    ><br />

    <label
      >What actions does your company take if a supply chain partner is
      found to have inadequate social or ethical practices?</label
    >
    <select name="supplyChainActions" required>
      <option value="a">
        Promptly communicate concerns with the supply chain partner, assess
        the severity and impact of the inadequate practices on the company's
        reputation and stakeholder expectations, collaborate with the
        partner to find solutions, conduct regular audits or inspections to
        verify compliance and share results transparently, consider
        alternative suppliers if the partner fails to show significant
        progress.
      </option>
      <option value="b">
        Express concerns with the supply chain partner, but take limited
        action to address the inadequate practices, relying on the partner
        to self-correct without significant consequences.
      </option>
      <option value="c">
        Ignore or downplay concerns about the supply chain partner's
        inadequate practices, prioritizing cost or convenience over social
        and ethical considerations.
      </option></select
    ><br />

    <button type="submit" class="scale-up">Calculate ESG Score</button>
  </form>



